1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,224 --> 00:01:37,496
=Episode 15=
(Friends for Life)

3
00:01:39,860 --> 00:01:40,860
Yuxiu.

4
00:01:42,259 --> 00:01:44,060
Get better soon.

5
00:01:46,099 --> 00:01:48,379
I don't have much time left.

6
00:01:51,539 --> 00:01:53,060
I can't fulfill

7
00:01:53,220 --> 00:01:55,539
the promise we made back then.

8
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:00,899
How did I end up
owing you for a lifetime?

9
00:02:03,608 --> 00:02:08,120
(Qidaohezi People's Hospital, 1992)

10
00:02:33,659 --> 00:02:35,619
Mom, I brought the food.

11
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:37,580
Put it down, Xiaofei.

12
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,540
Xiaofei is here.

13
00:02:42,739 --> 00:02:45,860
Come and comb Auntie Yuxiu's hair.

14
00:02:46,552 --> 00:02:47,059
Okay.

15
00:02:47,059 --> 00:02:47,860
Hold it like this.

16
00:02:47,860 --> 00:02:48,580
Hold it.

17
00:02:50,739 --> 00:02:51,619
It's okay.

18
00:02:51,899 --> 00:02:54,100
He's Xiaofei.

19
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,459
Xiaofei will comb your hair.

20
00:02:55,779 --> 00:02:57,339
Comb slowly.

21
00:02:58,700 --> 00:02:59,580
Start from the top.

22
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:01,140
Comb like this. Comb slowly.

23
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:04,540
Comb down to the nape.

24
00:03:04,779 --> 00:03:05,939
Keep combing.

25
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:06,700
Okay.

26
00:03:07,059 --> 00:03:08,380
Got it? Like this.

27
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:09,980
Got it, Mom.

28
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:11,779
Chat with her.

29
00:03:12,339 --> 00:03:13,179
Okay, Mom.

30
00:03:13,339 --> 00:03:16,140
Tell Auntie Yuxiu some stories.

31
00:03:18,779 --> 00:03:20,459
Auntie Yuxiu, I'll comb slowly.

32
00:03:20,860 --> 00:03:22,219
Don't be scared.

33
00:03:25,499 --> 00:03:27,619
Auntie Yuxiu, let me tell you a story.

34
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:31,059
My mom used to tell me

35
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:33,459
a story about a rabbit and a turtle.

36
00:04:17,848 --> 00:04:18,744
(Autopsy Report)

37
00:04:20,779 --> 00:04:23,099
The victim died
from a cervical fracture,

38
00:04:23,099 --> 00:04:24,419
which led to asphyxiation.

39
00:04:25,219 --> 00:04:26,099
He was strangled.

40
00:04:26,539 --> 00:04:27,419
With what?

41
00:04:27,704 --> 00:04:28,820
(1.21 Corpse Concealment Case
Special Task Force)

42
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:31,339
It's been 31 days
since the remains were discovered.

43
00:04:32,859 --> 00:04:34,979
This case is quite old.

44
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,700
So the only valid clues

45
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:38,899
(Pen)
are the pen and the leaves.

46
00:04:38,899 --> 00:04:39,500
(Wen Yuxiu)

47
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,339
(Remains, dying of asphyxiation, leaves)
So we can't overlook

48
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:43,140
any suspicious point.

49
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:45,580
The pen

50
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:48,099
(Wen Yuxiu is Zhou Yun)
led us to Wen Yuxiu.

51
00:04:48,099 --> 00:04:48,940
(Body concealment case)

52
00:04:48,940 --> 00:04:50,219
We've found Wen Yuxiu.

53
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,459
Evidence shows

54
00:04:53,219 --> 00:04:56,219
that we can rule out
her involvement in this case.

55
00:04:57,140 --> 00:05:00,140
I think we need to focus
on the two pieces of evidence.

56
00:05:00,580 --> 00:05:02,140
The pen and the leaves.

57
00:05:02,979 --> 00:05:04,299
Pursue a new line of inquiry.

58
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:07,140
Keep looking into everything.

59
00:05:08,539 --> 00:05:10,580
Ms. Zhou is back in Qidaohezi.

60
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:11,700
She's in the hospital.

61
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:13,580
Xiaoming's family is looking after her.

62
00:05:15,539 --> 00:05:17,060
Thank you for bringing her back.

63
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,219
Won't you visit her?

64
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:22,740
When I have time.

65
00:05:23,419 --> 00:05:24,899
You're avoiding Ren Xiaoming, huh?

66
00:05:27,180 --> 00:05:28,779
Her copyright lawsuit

67
00:05:28,779 --> 00:05:30,700
was probably delayed
because of Ms. Zhou.

68
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:31,740
Otherwise...

69
00:05:32,539 --> 00:05:33,979
Why do you keep mentioning her?

70
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:35,099
Are you two close?

71
00:05:36,979 --> 00:05:39,419
We weren't in the same class
back in high school.

72
00:05:40,419 --> 00:05:42,099
She always came looking for you.

73
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,260
When you took a leave,
she kept asking me about you.

74
00:05:45,659 --> 00:05:46,700
Why are you helping her?

75
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:48,260
I'm not.

76
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:51,219
I'm helping her
because she's your friend.

77
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,659
You've got me all confused.

78
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,299
Let's sort it out.

79
00:05:56,140 --> 00:05:56,952
I want to help you.

80
00:05:57,380 --> 00:05:58,459
I want you two to make up.

81
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,580
Why are you helping me?

82
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:00,920
Do you see me as your friend?

83
00:06:03,339 --> 00:06:05,539
Remember how you
lectured the kid who ranked 59th

84
00:06:05,779 --> 00:06:08,180
in the hallway of the dorm

85
00:06:08,419 --> 00:06:10,539
back when we were in tenth grade?

86
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:12,979
I really admired you.

87
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:15,339
I thought you'd make a great friend.

88
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:29,859
I made this congee perfectly.

89
00:06:34,620 --> 00:06:35,380
Xiaoyu.

90
00:06:36,580 --> 00:06:38,260
Bring me your mom's phone.

91
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:39,459
Okay.

92
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:41,659
Have plenty of congee.

93
00:06:42,779 --> 00:06:43,299
Here you go.

94
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,299
Thank you.

95
00:06:45,752 --> 00:06:46,904
(Ren Xiaoming,
Request to add you as a friend)

96
00:06:49,112 --> 00:06:51,352
(Ren Xiaoming,
Request to add you as a friend)

97
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,219
Why did you contact Ren Xiaoming?

98
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:04,419
You know how much I hate her.

99
00:07:06,979 --> 00:07:08,568
Who said you could look at my phone?

100
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:14,008
Give it to me.

101
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:17,380
I didn't accept her friend request.

102
00:07:18,299 --> 00:07:19,459
I won't contact her.

103
00:07:20,099 --> 00:07:20,940
I won't see her.

104
00:07:23,060 --> 00:07:25,260
Because I won't
give you devil the chance

105
00:07:25,979 --> 00:07:27,659
to hurt anyone around me.

106
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:31,700
Don't forget

107
00:07:34,219 --> 00:07:35,700
what I have on you.

108
00:07:40,099 --> 00:07:42,299
Grandma, what do you have?

109
00:07:46,419 --> 00:07:50,060
I have a little hold over your mom.

110
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:53,820
I want to check it out.

111
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:57,099
Alright, as long as you behave,

112
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:00,539
I will show you.

113
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:03,219
Go wash your hands.

114
00:08:03,580 --> 00:08:04,140
Okay.

115
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,459
Li Meng gave me her phone number.

116
00:08:33,699 --> 00:08:34,779
(Ren Xiaoming.)

117
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:37,179
(The person I hate the most)

118
00:08:37,899 --> 00:08:39,220
(is back again.)

119
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,136
(Qidaohezi, 2006)

120
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,064
(Taxi)

121
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,100
Ren Xiaoming.

122
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,620
Ren Xiaoming.

123
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,220
Xiaoming.

124
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:58,579
Bai Shu. He Yuqiong.

125
00:08:58,620 --> 00:08:59,659
- Zhang Fang.
- Xiaoming.

126
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,220
Xiaoming.

127
00:09:12,620 --> 00:09:13,939
Welcome home.

128
00:09:17,179 --> 00:09:18,460
Warm welcome.

129
00:09:18,539 --> 00:09:19,860
Welcome home.

130
00:09:20,299 --> 00:09:21,179
Hello, Auntie.

131
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:24,179
We're back.

132
00:09:24,779 --> 00:09:26,340
Auntie, I'm here to help you move.

133
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:27,860
No need to make it so formal.

134
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,020
Auntie, I'm here to help as well.

135
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,299
I'm treating everyone to dumplings.

136
00:09:32,299 --> 00:09:32,860
Dumplings.

137
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:33,419
- Auntie.
- Nice!

138
00:09:33,579 --> 00:09:34,620
I want lamb dumplings.

139
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:36,179
No problem. Strong young man.

140
00:09:36,179 --> 00:09:36,860
Hurry up.

141
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,419
I'll do it.

142
00:09:37,419 --> 00:09:38,179
Let me do it.

143
00:09:38,179 --> 00:09:39,299
- Leave it.
- It's fine.

144
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:40,699
What are you doing?

145
00:09:40,699 --> 00:09:41,620
Let's go.

146
00:09:42,699 --> 00:09:43,740
Let's go.

147
00:09:51,699 --> 00:09:52,579
Don't run.

148
00:09:55,659 --> 00:09:57,340
The keys are here.

149
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:00,020
Open the door.

150
00:10:00,059 --> 00:10:00,939
Mom, open the door.

151
00:10:01,419 --> 00:10:02,899
Opening up.

152
00:10:04,179 --> 00:10:05,140
Come in.

153
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:05,860
Thank you, Auntie.

154
00:10:07,819 --> 00:10:08,419
Thank you.

155
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,819
It's good to have you back.

156
00:10:15,899 --> 00:10:17,419
I can come over for meals again.

157
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,939
My mom will be thrilled
to hear you say that.

158
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:24,819
But,

159
00:10:25,299 --> 00:10:27,539
she probably doesn't even
have 100 yuan right now.

160
00:10:29,299 --> 00:10:32,059
She's acting tough beyond her means.

161
00:10:32,579 --> 00:10:34,179
Let's see how she gets by.

162
00:10:35,779 --> 00:10:37,220
Don't worry about money.

163
00:10:37,899 --> 00:10:38,579
I've got this.

164
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:40,699
Come on.

165
00:10:41,939 --> 00:10:44,020
How much can you make from writing?

166
00:10:44,779 --> 00:10:45,819
Don't worry about me.

167
00:10:47,299 --> 00:10:48,340
But I think

168
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:50,659
moving out and back in

169
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:52,659
is pretty embarrassing.

170
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:57,100
Zhang Fang used to call me a tagalong.

171
00:10:58,299 --> 00:10:59,620
Now nobody dares say it.

172
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:03,819
But I know what they're thinking.

173
00:11:05,299 --> 00:11:06,980
Who knows how far the gossip has spread?

174
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:10,779
You're so afraid of gossip.

175
00:11:12,059 --> 00:11:14,140
But you tell me all your family secrets.

176
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:16,899
You're different, of course.

177
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:17,980
We're best friends.

178
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:21,299
No matter what you think,

179
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:22,899
I don't mind telling you

180
00:11:23,699 --> 00:11:25,299
anything embarrassing.

181
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:29,699
Because I know you'll never laugh at me.

182
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,620
You'll always be on my side.

183
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:33,020
You too.

184
00:11:33,659 --> 00:11:35,100
You're always on my side.

185
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,220
Absolutely.

186
00:11:42,939 --> 00:11:45,299
You're commuting
between La City and Qidaohezi.

187
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:47,179
That's so far. How inconvenient.

188
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:55,179
It's okay. You don't have to tell me.

189
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:56,779
I won't pry into it.

190
00:11:59,699 --> 00:12:00,340
Xiaoming.

191
00:12:01,699 --> 00:12:02,980
I do have a secret.

192
00:12:05,899 --> 00:12:07,179
I know you have a secret

193
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,779
that you don't want to say.

194
00:12:10,779 --> 00:12:12,699
It's fine.
Double standards are okay for you.

195
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:15,100
I can't have secrets from you,
but you can.

196
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:18,260
No double standards.

197
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:20,696
But

198
00:12:22,779 --> 00:12:23,740
if I tell you...

199
00:12:23,819 --> 00:12:24,620
I swear

200
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:25,980
I wouldn't laugh at you.

201
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:27,620
It's not that.

202
00:12:30,179 --> 00:12:31,140
Don't pity me.

203
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,659
Don't look at me with sympathy.

204
00:12:38,488 --> 00:12:40,220
What is it?

205
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:47,899
Come to my house.

206
00:12:48,299 --> 00:12:49,220
You'll find out.

207
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,860
Here, change into slippers.

208
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:01,779
Your bag.

209
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:08,460
Your place is so fancy.
We need to change into slippers.

210
00:13:15,740 --> 00:13:17,220
Your home is so big.

211
00:13:17,819 --> 00:13:19,860
You've never invited me over.

212
00:13:20,059 --> 00:13:20,980
This isn't my home.

213
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:23,579
It's my cage.

214
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:26,740
Got it.

215
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:29,659
The place in La City
wasn't my home either.

216
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:33,179
Change your slippers.

217
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,140
Again?

218
00:13:39,539 --> 00:13:40,500
She made the rules.

219
00:13:43,380 --> 00:13:44,419
Her slippers?

220
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:47,500
I won't wear them.

221
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:03,779
This is your bedroom?

222
00:14:05,939 --> 00:14:08,500
Look, doesn't it look like a fish tank?

223
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:12,819
Don't pity me.

224
00:14:15,939 --> 00:14:17,419
I didn't dare tell you my secret,

225
00:14:19,179 --> 00:14:20,579
because I was afraid

226
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:22,579
you'd pity me if you knew.

227
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:24,899
You've overestimated my kindness.

228
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,819
I have no energy left to pity you.

229
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,460
Your bedroom

230
00:14:35,380 --> 00:14:36,740
may look like a fish tank,

231
00:14:37,539 --> 00:14:39,819
but your bed is way better than my sofa.

232
00:14:43,740 --> 00:14:44,899
Come on, tell me.

233
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:47,380
What's your secret?

234
00:14:47,819 --> 00:14:49,220
I promise I won't pity you.

235
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,819
I'm not Ge Wenjun's biological child.

236
00:14:59,419 --> 00:15:00,179
She is.

237
00:15:05,419 --> 00:15:06,899
For real?

238
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:13,620
On June 1, 1977,

239
00:15:15,460 --> 00:15:16,980
Ge Wenjun's daughter was born.

240
00:15:18,699 --> 00:15:19,699
She named her Bai Shu.

241
00:15:22,939 --> 00:15:24,140
But sadly, that girl

242
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,460
died on her twelfth birthday.

243
00:15:34,419 --> 00:15:37,299
The tombstone in Rest Cemetery
is for her real daughter?

244
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:43,980
She gave me the same name,

245
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:47,860
made me wear her clothes,

246
00:15:48,899 --> 00:15:50,220
eat her favorite foods,

247
00:15:51,819 --> 00:15:53,299
play her piano,

248
00:15:54,819 --> 00:15:56,140
and celebrate her birthday.

249
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:01,299
But I'm not allowed to sleep in her bed.

250
00:16:02,659 --> 00:16:05,419
So Ge Wenjun made me
this fish tank instead.

251
00:16:07,419 --> 00:16:08,699
She controls the curtain.

252
00:16:09,299 --> 00:16:10,899
The time when I sleep, get up,

253
00:16:11,779 --> 00:16:14,659
eat, and study is all under her control.

254
00:16:16,779 --> 00:16:17,659
She just sits there,

255
00:16:18,779 --> 00:16:20,020
watching my every move.

256
00:16:26,699 --> 00:16:27,579
Pajamas,

257
00:16:28,299 --> 00:16:31,659
slippers, towels, and toothbrushes
all come in mother-daughter sets.

258
00:16:33,819 --> 00:16:36,020
Different places
require different slippers.

259
00:16:38,579 --> 00:16:39,939
Those are for the bedroom.

260
00:16:41,299 --> 00:16:42,899
These are for upstairs.

261
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:47,260
And the bathroom has its own pair.

262
00:16:51,020 --> 00:16:53,779
So many slippers.
What if you wear the wrong ones?

263
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:57,819
I get punished.

264
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:01,860
How?

265
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,139
Start everything over.

266
00:17:08,299 --> 00:17:10,744
Change into slippers,
take a bath, and use the restroom.

267
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:14,299
Everywhere she stepped,
she'd clean it herself,

268
00:17:15,779 --> 00:17:16,900
kneeling on the floor.

269
00:17:18,299 --> 00:17:19,859
She'd make me stand and watch

270
00:17:21,819 --> 00:17:23,020
and let me

271
00:17:24,059 --> 00:17:27,059
apologize over and over.

272
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,299
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

273
00:17:43,059 --> 00:17:44,379
You were only this big.

274
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:48,059
I changed your diapers,

275
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:51,420
fed you, and raised you
to this very day.

276
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,379
You had a congenital heart defect.

277
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:01,619
I gave away all my money

278
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:04,579
to find the best doctor
for your surgery.

279
00:18:05,299 --> 00:18:07,220
When you caught a cold and had a fever,

280
00:18:09,180 --> 00:18:10,660
I wouldn't eat or sleep

281
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:12,660
and stayed by your side day and night

282
00:18:12,779 --> 00:18:14,059
until you got better.

283
00:18:16,339 --> 00:18:17,980
I drove you to school

284
00:18:18,299 --> 00:18:20,460
and picked you up, no matter how cold

285
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:23,660
or hot it is,

286
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:26,859
without missing a single day.

287
00:18:28,539 --> 00:18:30,539
Can you find a better mother than me?

288
00:18:35,339 --> 00:18:37,740
Can you find one?

289
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:44,299
The food you eat, the clothes you wear,
and the things you use

290
00:18:44,859 --> 00:18:47,220
are the best in all of Qidaohezi!

291
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:50,099
Your classmates admire and envy you,

292
00:18:50,299 --> 00:18:52,020
not because you are pretty.

293
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,020
It's because of me.

294
00:18:54,859 --> 00:18:57,779
As your mother,

295
00:18:58,819 --> 00:19:00,299
I searched all over the country

296
00:19:00,299 --> 00:19:02,460
to buy you the prettiest clothes.

297
00:19:03,299 --> 00:19:06,139
Shanghai, Shenzhen, Guangzhou...

298
00:19:06,940 --> 00:19:08,339
I looked everywhere.

299
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:09,379
And you?

300
00:19:11,299 --> 00:19:13,059
How did you treat me?

301
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:19,740
You exploited my motherly love,

302
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,059
deceived me,

303
00:19:23,859 --> 00:19:25,420
and hurt me.

304
00:19:27,260 --> 00:19:28,260
I'm sorry.

305
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,339
Why?

306
00:19:39,619 --> 00:19:41,980
How could you bear to do this?

307
00:19:45,779 --> 00:19:47,379
How could you?

308
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:52,859
How could you?

309
00:19:53,180 --> 00:19:55,460
I'm your mom.

310
00:19:57,859 --> 00:19:59,980
- How could you do this to me?
- I'm sorry.

311
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:03,220
I'm sorry. I was wrong.

312
00:20:03,539 --> 00:20:04,460
I was wrong.

313
00:20:05,299 --> 00:20:06,539
Bai Shu.

314
00:20:07,099 --> 00:20:09,460
You're all I have left.

315
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:12,339
Please don't treat me like this.

316
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:16,740
You're all I have now.

317
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:23,579
I'm sorry.

318
00:20:24,579 --> 00:20:26,779
Say "Mom, I'm sorry."

319
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:29,020
Say "Mom."

320
00:20:29,299 --> 00:20:30,980
Say "Mom."

321
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:47,500
(You're a devil.
Sooner or later, I'll leave you.)

322
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,460
Who wrote this?

323
00:20:49,619 --> 00:20:51,059
Her biological daughter, Bai Shu.

324
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,220
I found it in primary school.

325
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:57,139
I haven't been able
to call her "Mom" since that day.

326
00:21:00,339 --> 00:21:03,500
Do you think she killed her daughter?

327
00:21:04,379 --> 00:21:06,059
Or drove to death, to say the least.

328
00:21:08,299 --> 00:21:09,660
I saw the death certificate.

329
00:21:11,619 --> 00:21:13,299
It said accidental fall.

330
00:21:13,779 --> 00:21:15,059
Not homicide or suicide.

331
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:16,220
That's creepy.

332
00:21:20,859 --> 00:21:22,139
I often have the same dream

333
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:25,020
where the fish tank
is filled with water.

334
00:21:26,059 --> 00:21:28,180
I fail to swim out and end up drowning.

335
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:33,500
Don't worry. I won't let you die.

336
00:21:58,379 --> 00:21:59,220
How about this?

337
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:02,260
Don't live at home.

338
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:05,379
Move out and live with me.

339
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,260
We'll rent a place near the school.

340
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:12,099
Lots of students who live far away

341
00:22:12,779 --> 00:22:13,779
rent places too.

342
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:16,619
That's impossible.

343
00:22:17,339 --> 00:22:19,220
She'll try everything
to get me back home.

344
00:22:21,819 --> 00:22:22,740
One more year.

345
00:22:23,379 --> 00:22:24,660
Once I get into university,

346
00:22:26,379 --> 00:22:27,420
I can leave this place.

347
00:22:33,299 --> 00:22:36,460
Have you ever thought about
your biological parents?

348
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:41,139
They might be
searching everywhere for you.

349
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,980
Do you want to look for them?

350
00:22:47,099 --> 00:22:48,339
Someday I will find them.

351
00:22:49,099 --> 00:22:51,700
They're like a missing piece of my life.

352
00:22:53,579 --> 00:22:54,619
Once I put it in place,

353
00:22:56,660 --> 00:22:57,940
my life will be complete.

354
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,420
I'll stand by you.

355
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:17,220
Xiaoming.

356
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,660
You finally came to visit. Welcome.

357
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:26,339
Bai Shu, why don't you
get Xiaoming some snacks?

358
00:23:26,819 --> 00:23:29,099
She just got here. We're about to study.

359
00:23:29,339 --> 00:23:30,339
So I haven't had time.

360
00:23:31,819 --> 00:23:33,379
Go ahead and study.

361
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,020
Never mind.

362
00:23:35,700 --> 00:23:36,779
I must head home now.

363
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:38,460
Or I'll miss the last bus.

364
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:41,779
How come you're leaving so soon?

365
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:43,539
Why don't you

366
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:45,539
stay over with Bai Shu?

367
00:23:46,339 --> 00:23:49,139
Tomorrow morning,
I'll drop you both off at school.

368
00:23:50,619 --> 00:23:51,779
No need to trouble you.

369
00:23:53,339 --> 00:23:54,339
I'm off, Bai Shu.

370
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:56,099
Wait.

371
00:23:57,740 --> 00:23:59,020
It'll be dark soon.

372
00:24:00,139 --> 00:24:01,859
If something happens on the way,

373
00:24:02,059 --> 00:24:03,660
your mom will blame me.

374
00:24:05,619 --> 00:24:06,779
It's just a quick drive.

375
00:24:07,220 --> 00:24:09,420
Come on, I'll drive you.

376
00:24:32,059 --> 00:24:33,099
Put on the slippers.

377
00:24:50,139 --> 00:24:52,139
Stay away from Bai Shu.

378
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:55,020
She doesn't need a friend like you.

379
00:24:57,619 --> 00:24:58,700
You're not my mom.

380
00:24:58,819 --> 00:24:59,992
Don't tell me what to do.

381
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,859
You can't decide
what kind of friends she needs.

382
00:25:03,139 --> 00:25:04,260
It's her call.

383
00:25:16,099 --> 00:25:16,819
Get out.

384
00:25:18,740 --> 00:25:19,859
I'll tell others

385
00:25:21,059 --> 00:25:22,579
that you were being rude.

386
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:24,500
You argued with me in the car,

387
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:27,020
insisted I stop,

388
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,539
and then ran off as soon as you got out.

389
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:32,819
You don't have to lie.

390
00:25:34,339 --> 00:25:35,900
I don't want to ride in your junker.

391
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,299
You think you can scare me like this?

392
00:25:38,859 --> 00:25:39,660
I'm telling you.

393
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:42,220
Bai Shu and I
will be best friends for life.

394
00:25:42,819 --> 00:25:44,940
I'll take her anywhere she wants to go.

395
00:25:45,420 --> 00:25:47,339
I'll also help her
find her biological parents.

396
00:25:55,299 --> 00:25:56,059
Ren Xiaoming.

397
00:25:57,819 --> 00:26:00,579
You will pay for what you just said.

398
00:26:01,819 --> 00:26:02,740
Try me.

399
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:07,180
Get out.

400
00:26:16,299 --> 00:26:17,299
Like I care.

401
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:19,339
I've walked home at night.

402
00:26:20,099 --> 00:26:21,139
Think you can scare me?

403
00:26:34,456 --> 00:26:37,220
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
Have you seen Ms. Zhou's pen again?

404
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:38,619
Only once.

405
00:26:39,819 --> 00:26:40,700
When was that?

406
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:43,139
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2004)
Take it.

407
00:26:44,220 --> 00:26:45,688
If she didn't want it, neither do I.

408
00:26:50,099 --> 00:26:51,779
Why do you keep asking about that pen?

409
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:54,099
Just curious.

410
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,339
(She can't be just curious.)

411
00:26:59,020 --> 00:27:00,180
(Seems I need to speed up.)

412
00:27:00,859 --> 00:27:02,139
You got a visitor.

413
00:27:03,339 --> 00:27:04,099
Is it a good time?

414
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:05,500
Good to see you, Xiaoming.

415
00:27:05,539 --> 00:27:06,059
Welcome.

416
00:27:06,339 --> 00:27:07,740
I'm just taking a lunch break.

417
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:09,660
I brought you something.

418
00:27:10,072 --> 00:27:11,859
Why did you bring gifts?

419
00:27:12,500 --> 00:27:13,740
What did you get?

420
00:27:13,859 --> 00:27:14,819
This isn't a bribe.

421
00:27:14,819 --> 00:27:16,059
These are for my nephew.

422
00:27:16,139 --> 00:27:17,859
Oh my, let me see.

423
00:27:18,619 --> 00:27:20,500
There's even a breast pump?

424
00:27:21,099 --> 00:27:23,260
But you haven't had kids.
How do you know?

425
00:27:23,260 --> 00:27:24,660
I searched online like crazy.

426
00:27:24,859 --> 00:27:26,180
My eyes are practically crossed.

427
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,660
Really? Can you see me?

428
00:27:28,859 --> 00:27:30,900
Well, thanks from your nephew.

429
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:36,059
It's worth it.
You'll use these when you get pregnant.

430
00:27:36,779 --> 00:27:37,660
Me?

431
00:27:40,819 --> 00:27:41,779
I haven't decided yet.

432
00:27:42,859 --> 00:27:44,420
That's what I said back then.

433
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,339
Ten people say they won't have kids,

434
00:27:46,339 --> 00:27:47,940
and nine end up being doting parents.

435
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:49,660
Stop fussing.

436
00:27:51,059 --> 00:27:51,900
Have some water.

437
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:53,220
Sit.

438
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:54,099
Sit.

439
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:01,660
What's up?

440
00:28:02,299 --> 00:28:05,299
I just wanted to ask
if we can bring Yamei back.

441
00:28:05,819 --> 00:28:08,420
No, she's not eighteen yet.

442
00:28:09,099 --> 00:28:12,139
Even if you guys are close with her mom,

443
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:13,900
you're not the legal guardians.

444
00:28:14,460 --> 00:28:17,220
Don't worry. I'm keeping an eye on her.

445
00:28:17,220 --> 00:28:18,180
I'm counting on you.

446
00:28:18,379 --> 00:28:19,299
Rest assured.

447
00:28:25,059 --> 00:28:25,779
Anything else?

448
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:33,020
Yeah, there is one more thing

449
00:28:33,539 --> 00:28:34,619
I need your help with.

450
00:28:36,059 --> 00:28:36,700
Tell me.

451
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,619
You see, I don't live here.

452
00:28:39,099 --> 00:28:40,299
Work keeps me busy.

453
00:28:41,339 --> 00:28:43,020
And I might be going on a long trip.

454
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,299
Would it be possible for you

455
00:28:46,099 --> 00:28:47,379
to check in on my place

456
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:50,260
and look after my mom and Xiaofei?

457
00:28:51,139 --> 00:28:52,339
You sounded serious.

458
00:28:52,339 --> 00:28:54,139
You were building up to just this?

459
00:28:56,299 --> 00:28:57,139
You can count on me.

460
00:28:57,539 --> 00:28:58,579
Thank you.

461
00:28:59,059 --> 00:28:59,740
Again?

462
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:00,900
We're all family here.

463
00:29:01,099 --> 00:29:01,980
Stop thanking me.

464
00:29:02,139 --> 00:29:03,619
When my dad got into trouble,

465
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:05,619
you guys sold your house
to cover his debt.

466
00:29:06,220 --> 00:29:07,220
I hate to bring it up.

467
00:29:07,299 --> 00:29:08,339
I just feel

468
00:29:08,539 --> 00:29:09,539
that all these years,

469
00:29:09,940 --> 00:29:11,859
you guys must have had it really tough.

470
00:29:12,139 --> 00:29:13,539
Don't you know my mom?

471
00:29:13,740 --> 00:29:15,859
She survives anything like a cockroach.

472
00:29:16,568 --> 00:29:21,112
(Qidaohezi, 2006)

473
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:30,299
Ren Xiaoming.

474
00:29:31,180 --> 00:29:32,260
Ren Xiaoming.

475
00:29:36,339 --> 00:29:38,139
Ren Xiaofei, time for another big job.

476
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:44,099
Why are you stockpiling food?

477
00:29:44,099 --> 00:29:45,260
I'm starting a business.

478
00:29:46,619 --> 00:29:47,500
Selling flour?

479
00:29:49,260 --> 00:29:50,819
I'm not selling flour.

480
00:29:51,940 --> 00:29:54,779
I'm entering
the food processing industry.

481
00:29:56,020 --> 00:29:57,859
There are many constructions going on.

482
00:29:57,940 --> 00:29:58,940
It means

483
00:29:59,740 --> 00:30:00,379
there are sites.

484
00:30:00,619 --> 00:30:02,579
Besides, there are...

485
00:30:02,779 --> 00:30:03,339
Workers.

486
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:04,700
What do workers love to eat?

487
00:30:05,339 --> 00:30:06,059
Steamed buns.

488
00:30:06,339 --> 00:30:07,579
My boy's so smart.

489
00:30:08,420 --> 00:30:10,020
But your mom is even smarter.

490
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:11,379
I went out for a walk

491
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:13,299
and came up with this brilliant idea.

492
00:30:13,460 --> 00:30:14,740
Sell steamed buns to them.

493
00:30:15,059 --> 00:30:16,099
If 100 workers

494
00:30:16,260 --> 00:30:17,420
each eat three buns a day,

495
00:30:17,819 --> 00:30:19,220
that makes how many?

496
00:30:19,220 --> 00:30:19,896
Three hundred.

497
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:21,099
Bingo.

498
00:30:21,700 --> 00:30:23,339
If I make 10 cents per bun,

499
00:30:23,579 --> 00:30:24,660
300 buns would be...

500
00:30:25,379 --> 00:30:26,379
Thirty yuan.

501
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:27,579
Clever you.

502
00:30:27,779 --> 00:30:28,740
If I can sell buns

503
00:30:28,900 --> 00:30:30,500
at five construction sites,

504
00:30:30,660 --> 00:30:32,260
how much can I make in a month?

505
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:34,020
Nearly 5,000.

506
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:35,339
Be precise.

507
00:30:37,180 --> 00:30:39,299
At least 4,500. Easy math.

508
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,500
You're awesome.

509
00:30:41,059 --> 00:30:43,059
That's so sweet of you, pumping me up.

510
00:30:43,859 --> 00:30:45,299
You're not a balloon.

511
00:30:45,299 --> 00:30:46,740
Careful not to burst.

512
00:30:46,900 --> 00:30:49,020
Rascal, if I burst,
it'll be because of you.

513
00:30:49,260 --> 00:30:49,859
Get to work.

514
00:30:52,139 --> 00:30:53,859
Xiaofei, keep an eye out for me.

515
00:30:53,859 --> 00:30:54,500
Okay.

516
00:30:56,020 --> 00:30:56,632
Come on.

517
00:30:56,632 --> 00:30:57,220
Harder.

518
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:00,500
One, two, three.

519
00:31:01,099 --> 00:31:01,660
Go.

520
00:31:07,579 --> 00:31:08,139
Be careful.

521
00:31:09,339 --> 00:31:09,940
Easy.

522
00:31:15,379 --> 00:31:16,339
Seriously.

523
00:31:17,099 --> 00:31:18,220
Why'd they buy from you?

524
00:31:18,740 --> 00:31:21,139
I asked every restaurant nearby.

525
00:31:21,859 --> 00:31:24,299
The profit margin is too low,
so they won't bother.

526
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:27,859
The construction sites
can't make enough on the spot.

527
00:31:29,059 --> 00:31:31,379
Those workers would love to buy from me.

528
00:31:36,220 --> 00:31:37,299
By your calculations,

529
00:31:37,900 --> 00:31:40,260
we'd need to steam
over a thousand buns a day.

530
00:31:41,059 --> 00:31:42,819
Can our little stove handle that?

531
00:31:42,940 --> 00:31:45,139
It is a tough start.

532
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:47,420
But we have time.

533
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:50,980
They finish steaming
with ten pots in an hour.

534
00:31:51,220 --> 00:31:51,980
We have two pots.

535
00:31:52,420 --> 00:31:54,579
No need to calculate. Three hours.

536
00:31:55,379 --> 00:31:56,819
Or four hours if needed.

537
00:31:57,299 --> 00:31:58,299
We get up earlier.

538
00:31:58,740 --> 00:32:00,579
We can even skip sleep to make money.

539
00:32:01,099 --> 00:32:01,740
Good boy.

540
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,460
Why don't you stay awake and work?

541
00:32:06,099 --> 00:32:07,339
You sure have a lot to say.

542
00:32:08,420 --> 00:32:09,180
Let's go.

543
00:32:19,420 --> 00:32:20,299
I'll hold the bottom.

544
00:32:20,819 --> 00:32:21,579
Drag it.

545
00:33:12,980 --> 00:33:13,779
Xiaofei.

546
00:33:14,168 --> 00:33:15,619
Xiaofei, fire broke out!

547
00:33:15,619 --> 00:33:16,900
- Hurry.
- Stop yelling.

548
00:33:16,900 --> 00:33:18,139
Put out the fire! Hurry up.

549
00:33:19,339 --> 00:33:20,460
Stop yelling.

550
00:33:20,619 --> 00:33:21,299
There's no fire.

551
00:33:22,059 --> 00:33:23,260
Don't wake the neighbors.

552
00:33:27,859 --> 00:33:28,619
What time is it?

553
00:33:29,099 --> 00:33:29,779
4:30 AM?

554
00:33:30,379 --> 00:33:31,139
I got up at 2 AM.

555
00:33:31,299 --> 00:33:32,819
I've already steamed one batch.

556
00:33:32,819 --> 00:33:34,220
Look at the buns I steamed.

557
00:33:36,379 --> 00:33:36,980
My buns.

558
00:33:37,180 --> 00:33:37,740
Smell them.

559
00:33:37,740 --> 00:33:39,059
They smell amazing.

560
00:33:39,059 --> 00:33:39,940
I made it.

561
00:33:39,940 --> 00:33:40,740
They're ready.

562
00:33:40,740 --> 00:33:41,752
Have you lost your mind?

563
00:33:45,299 --> 00:33:46,539
Another batch is ready.

564
00:33:47,339 --> 00:33:48,299
The second batch.

565
00:33:49,900 --> 00:33:50,859
Stop holding that.

566
00:33:50,980 --> 00:33:51,740
Hurry up.

567
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:52,500
Come on.

568
00:33:54,980 --> 00:33:55,579
Alright.

569
00:33:55,940 --> 00:33:56,539
Come on.

570
00:33:57,379 --> 00:33:58,220
Stop kneading.

571
00:33:58,220 --> 00:33:58,859
Hurry.

572
00:33:58,940 --> 00:33:59,779
Go back to sleep.

573
00:33:59,779 --> 00:34:00,619
It's a school day.

574
00:34:01,099 --> 00:34:02,099
Xiaofei, go to sleep.

575
00:34:02,099 --> 00:34:02,940
Alright.

576
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:03,900
Go to sleep.

577
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:04,980
Go to sleep now.

578
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,500
The buns are ready. I'll take them out.

579
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:07,460
Who told you

580
00:34:07,619 --> 00:34:08,460
to stay up all night?

581
00:34:08,460 --> 00:34:09,300
Take the buns out.

582
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:11,579
Look at the mess you've made.

583
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:13,619
Go to sleep.

584
00:34:13,619 --> 00:34:14,380
Xiaofei, hurry.

585
00:34:14,380 --> 00:34:15,020
- Mom.
- Take her away.

586
00:34:15,020 --> 00:34:15,579
- My buns.
- Mom.

587
00:34:15,579 --> 00:34:16,300
Get some sleep.

588
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:17,020
She doesn't sleep,

589
00:34:17,139 --> 00:34:17,860
causing this mess.

590
00:34:18,020 --> 00:34:19,139
Mom, go to sleep.

591
00:34:19,500 --> 00:34:21,099
Take the buns out.

592
00:34:21,099 --> 00:34:21,659
Enough.

593
00:34:21,659 --> 00:34:22,940
I will sleep here.

594
00:34:24,860 --> 00:34:26,139
Take the buns out.

595
00:34:27,099 --> 00:34:27,900
Take them out.

596
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:30,940
Take them out.

597
00:34:34,659 --> 00:34:35,460
Take them out.

598
00:34:44,619 --> 00:34:47,219
Copper, aluminum, cans!

599
00:34:48,460 --> 00:34:51,340
Radiators, pistons, old batteries!

600
00:34:52,539 --> 00:34:55,699
Duck feathers,
goose feathers, long hair!

601
00:34:57,259 --> 00:34:59,900
Copper, aluminum, cans!

602
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:04,460
Radiators, pistons, old batteries!

603
00:35:05,699 --> 00:35:07,099
Duck feathers, goose feathers...

604
00:35:07,099 --> 00:35:08,539
Wake up, kids.

605
00:35:28,179 --> 00:35:29,059
Look.

606
00:35:29,259 --> 00:35:31,420
Look what it is.

607
00:35:32,219 --> 00:35:33,219
We're rich.

608
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:36,940
They bought all our big steamed buns.

609
00:35:37,860 --> 00:35:40,099
Xiaoming, we've found a way out.

610
00:35:42,940 --> 00:35:43,739
Xiaofei.

611
00:35:45,619 --> 00:35:47,500
Let's go. I'm not cooking lunch.

612
00:35:47,659 --> 00:35:48,408
We're eating out.

613
00:35:56,420 --> 00:35:57,460
Put on your nice clothes.

614
00:35:57,619 --> 00:35:58,940
I will put on my high heels.

615
00:36:06,780 --> 00:36:08,219
So hyped?

616
00:36:14,139 --> 00:36:15,579
Not far from death.

617
00:36:47,940 --> 00:36:49,460
Why are you up so early?

618
00:36:49,739 --> 00:36:50,860
Just one more month.

619
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:54,219
Once we make money, I'll buy a big stove
at the door

620
00:36:54,460 --> 00:36:55,219
and big steamers.

621
00:36:55,699 --> 00:36:57,219
Then we won't have to get up so early.

622
00:36:58,099 --> 00:36:59,980
Maybe you should just marry someone.

623
00:37:00,344 --> 00:37:00,940
I...

624
00:37:02,579 --> 00:37:05,099
I'm your only free labor now.

625
00:37:05,099 --> 00:37:06,420
Are you sure you want to hit me?

626
00:37:07,699 --> 00:37:09,059
Good girl.

627
00:37:10,020 --> 00:37:12,739
You're my only free labor.

628
00:37:13,139 --> 00:37:15,380
I need to butter you up.

629
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:20,259
Ren Xiaoming, I've decided.

630
00:37:21,659 --> 00:37:23,139
We're never moving again.

631
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:26,020
I'll take care of our family on my own.

632
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:27,619
On your own?

633
00:37:29,500 --> 00:37:31,300
How could I forget you?

634
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:33,259
You will help me.

635
00:37:37,739 --> 00:37:38,860
Did we wake the neighbors?

636
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:39,780
Go take a look.

637
00:37:47,219 --> 00:37:48,059
Why did you come?

638
00:37:48,539 --> 00:37:50,340
To make steamed buns with you.

639
00:37:51,340 --> 00:37:53,139
It's not even dawn yet.

640
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:54,296
Your mom doesn't mind?

641
00:37:54,699 --> 00:37:56,539
I told her yesterday
we had morning study

642
00:37:56,980 --> 00:37:59,020
and sneaked out
while she was still asleep.

643
00:37:59,940 --> 00:38:01,860
This is way too early.

644
00:38:01,940 --> 00:38:04,020
It's pitch black out. It's not safe.

645
00:38:04,420 --> 00:38:05,940
If you want to help me,

646
00:38:06,219 --> 00:38:08,300
come after lunch for the next batch.

647
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:09,059
Okay.

648
00:38:09,980 --> 00:38:12,219
You sure know how to
squeeze out the surplus value

649
00:38:12,539 --> 00:38:13,860
of free labor.

650
00:38:14,099 --> 00:38:14,904
I'm happy to help.

651
00:38:15,699 --> 00:38:17,860
She's happy to help. Two laborers.

652
00:38:50,900 --> 00:38:51,539
You're back?

653
00:38:52,219 --> 00:38:53,259
Wash your hands and eat.

654
00:39:40,420 --> 00:39:41,340
Where did you go?

655
00:39:42,940 --> 00:39:45,420
You go out every day
and come home so late.

656
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:49,980
I just went to read
at the Xinhua Bookstore.

657
00:39:50,619 --> 00:39:51,539
Xinhua Bookstore?

658
00:39:58,219 --> 00:39:58,808
Here.

659
00:40:04,300 --> 00:40:04,856
Here.

660
00:40:09,420 --> 00:40:10,860
Since when do they sell flour?

661
00:40:14,059 --> 00:40:16,340
I don't know where I got it.

662
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:20,440
Eat.

663
00:40:26,020 --> 00:40:26,900
I'm not very hungry.

664
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:28,380
You had leftovers from breakfast?

665
00:40:33,059 --> 00:40:33,980
Don't eat then.

666
00:40:51,672 --> 00:40:52,219
(Emergency Exit)

667
00:40:52,219 --> 00:40:54,659
You asked a retiring inspector

668
00:40:55,059 --> 00:40:56,020
like me

669
00:40:56,179 --> 00:40:57,139
to come take a look.

670
00:40:57,659 --> 00:40:58,420
What's the point?

671
00:40:59,179 --> 00:41:01,219
Mr. Ge, you're the expert in this.

672
00:41:01,539 --> 00:41:02,539
Now everyone knows

673
00:41:02,539 --> 00:41:05,139
that people in charge of QA
are your students.

674
00:41:06,099 --> 00:41:08,579
We feel reassured
to have you check for us.

675
00:41:08,659 --> 00:41:09,860
Don't beat around the bush.

676
00:41:11,179 --> 00:41:12,460
Want to use my connections

677
00:41:13,340 --> 00:41:14,980
to speed up your approval process?

678
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:17,780
I'm telling you.

679
00:41:18,579 --> 00:41:21,460
Forget about it
if there's a quality issue.

680
00:41:21,539 --> 00:41:23,619
The quality is top-notch.
Not a single flaw.

681
00:41:23,980 --> 00:41:26,259
Besides, cutting corners
when building houses costs lives.

682
00:41:26,456 --> 00:41:29,059
I wouldn't dare even if you tell me to.

683
00:41:31,139 --> 00:41:32,820
Quality first. Less chatter, okay?

684
00:41:33,020 --> 00:41:34,059
Absolutely.

685
00:41:35,460 --> 00:41:36,579
Well, it's mealtime.

686
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:37,539
Come on.

687
00:41:37,539 --> 00:41:38,980
We've prepared food for you.

688
00:41:39,139 --> 00:41:39,699
Let's eat.

689
00:41:39,699 --> 00:41:40,579
Four steamed buns.

690
00:41:40,579 --> 00:41:41,460
Forget it.

691
00:41:41,659 --> 00:41:42,219
Four buns.

692
00:41:42,219 --> 00:41:43,059
- Lobster.
- I'll look around.

693
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:44,219
And abalone.

694
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:45,420
I'll look around.

695
00:41:45,579 --> 00:41:46,659
Two steamed buns.

696
00:41:47,340 --> 00:41:48,380
- Have a bite.
- Two steamed buns.

697
00:41:48,699 --> 00:41:50,259
I told you. I'll look around.

698
00:41:50,460 --> 00:41:52,020
Two steamed buns.

699
00:41:52,579 --> 00:41:53,304
- How many?
- Let's go.

700
00:41:53,304 --> 00:41:53,900
Two buns.

701
00:41:53,900 --> 00:41:55,160
- Two steamed buns.
- Come on.

702
00:41:57,980 --> 00:41:58,776
Two steamed buns.

703
00:41:58,900 --> 00:41:59,579
Two buns.

704
00:41:59,940 --> 00:42:00,820
How much are these?

705
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,820
Two for one yuan. Good price.

706
00:42:03,139 --> 00:42:04,579
I'm not illegally vending here.

707
00:42:04,820 --> 00:42:05,980
The construction site agreed.

708
00:42:06,179 --> 00:42:07,420
It's a convenience service.

709
00:42:07,420 --> 00:42:08,579
You're Xiaoming's mom?

710
00:42:09,900 --> 00:42:10,488
Yeah.

711
00:42:11,460 --> 00:42:12,539
- Two steamed buns.
- Two.

712
00:42:12,539 --> 00:42:13,780
I'm Bai Shu's mother.

713
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:16,739
We've met at parent-teacher meetings.

714
00:42:17,340 --> 00:42:18,380
I remember now.

715
00:42:19,059 --> 00:42:19,980
What a coincidence.

716
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:20,940
Two buns?

717
00:42:20,940 --> 00:42:21,720
Yeah.

718
00:42:22,820 --> 00:42:24,179
Weren't you in La City?

719
00:42:24,340 --> 00:42:25,259
I moved back.

720
00:42:25,259 --> 00:42:25,820
Two buns?

721
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:26,460
Two.

722
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:27,900
That's exact.

723
00:42:28,179 --> 00:42:29,420
You made these buns?

724
00:42:29,940 --> 00:42:30,539
Yeah.

725
00:42:31,340 --> 00:42:32,699
Just trying to make a living.

726
00:42:33,820 --> 00:42:34,940
What are you doing here?

727
00:42:35,579 --> 00:42:36,300
Two buns.

728
00:42:36,300 --> 00:42:36,952
Two buns?

729
00:42:37,699 --> 00:42:39,699
They invited me
to inspect the construction.

730
00:42:41,020 --> 00:42:42,380
So you're the supervisor here?

731
00:42:43,780 --> 00:42:44,619
Not at all.

732
00:42:46,579 --> 00:42:49,539
They're just trying
to squeeze the last drop out of me.

733
00:42:51,259 --> 00:42:52,739
If you run into any problems,

734
00:42:53,699 --> 00:42:54,460
let me know.

735
00:42:55,139 --> 00:42:55,980
I'll do my best

736
00:42:56,380 --> 00:42:57,579
- to help.
- Two steamed buns.

737
00:42:57,619 --> 00:42:58,539
That's great.

738
00:42:59,340 --> 00:43:02,139
Bai Shu comes to help knead the dough.
And you're so supportive.

739
00:43:02,139 --> 00:43:02,940
Your change.

740
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
